cast_shell: keep the aura compositor background opaque

Without this patch, the wl_surface state machine on cast_shell wedges
with GPU compositing enabled: weston sends xdg_surface.configure and
chromium never sends ack_configure because viz never produces a
wl_buffer the wayland host can record. The workaround was
--disable-gpu-compositing in the launcher, which routes the final
composite through Skia software and costs ~10-29% of one A53 core for
animation-heavy workloads. This patch removes the wedge so GPU
compositing can be left on.

Root cause: chromecast/graphics/cast_window_manager_aura.cc sets the
aura compositor's background colour to SK_ColorTRANSPARENT
unconditionally with the comment "Allow seeing through to the hardware
video plane". That plane only exists on cast hardware with a real HW
video underlay; bridgething is a kiosk over wayland with no video
underlay path, so the transparency only ever serves to wedge frame
production.

The mechanism, traced through chromium 147:

  1. compositor->SetBackgroundColor(SK_ColorTRANSPARENT) propagates
     into cc::LayerTreeImpl::background_color_, alpha = 0.

  2. cc::LayerTreeHostImpl::AppendQuadsToFillScreen
     (cc/trees/layer_tree_host_impl.cc) early-returns when
     screen_background_color.fA == 0, so no SolidColor quads are
     emitted for the fill region.

  3. Before the renderer paints its first frame, that fill region IS
     the whole surface. The AggregatedFrame submitted to viz contains
     no quads.

  4. viz's Display compositor takes the empty frame through the GPU
     output surface (SkiaRenderer + OverlayProcessorOzone) and produces
     no wl_buffer for it. config.buffer_id stays 0 on the resulting
     WaylandFrame.

  5. WaylandFrameManager::MaybeProcessPendingFrame
     (ui/ozone/platform/wayland/host/wayland_frame_manager.cc) only
     calls OnSequencePoint, which is what advances the configure-ack
     state, when (!frame->buffer_lost && !!config.buffer_id) or
     should_ack_swap_without_commit_. With buffer_id = 0 and no
     ack-without-commit flag, the ack never fires, the wl_surface
     stays unmapped, no buffer attaches, the panel keeps showing
     weston-desktop-shell's background.

The software output device (SoftwareRenderer behind
--disable-gpu-compositing) takes a different swap path that always
produces a buffer regardless of damage state, which is why the
workaround unwedged the pipe.

Setting the compositor backstop to SK_ColorBLACK (alpha = 255) makes
AppendQuadsToFillScreen emit a full-screen SolidColorDrawQuad on every
frame until the renderer covers the surface. viz now has content for
the first frame, the GPU output surface produces a wl_buffer, the ack
fires, the wl_surface gets mapped, GPU compositing carries from then
on. Black before the first paint is fine for this device; the panel's
default is black and the bridgething theme is dark.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [kiosk-specific use case]

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>

--- a/chromecast/graphics/cast_window_manager_aura.cc
+++ b/chromecast/graphics/cast_window_manager_aura.cc
@@ -197,8 +197,18 @@
       std::make_unique<CastLayoutManager>(this, root_window));
   window_tree_host_->SetRootTransform(GetPrimaryDisplayRotationTransform());
 
-  // Allow seeing through to the hardware video plane:
-  window_tree_host_->compositor()->SetBackgroundColor(SK_ColorTRANSPARENT);
+  // bridgething patch: keep the compositor backstop opaque (black).
+  // Upstream sets SK_ColorTRANSPARENT to see through to a hardware
+  // video plane, which bridgething does not have. With alpha = 0
+  // cc::LayerTreeHostImpl::AppendQuadsToFillScreen early-returns and
+  // emits no quads for the fill region; before the renderer's first
+  // paint the AggregatedFrame is empty, the GPU output surface
+  // produces no wl_buffer, and WaylandFrameManager never gets a frame
+  // with config.buffer_id != 0 to advance OnSequencePoint /
+  // ack_configure. Opaque black gives viz a full-screen
+  // SolidColorDrawQuad to draw, so the configure handshake completes
+  // on the first frame.
+  window_tree_host_->compositor()->SetBackgroundColor(SK_ColorBLACK);
 
   focus_client_ = std::make_unique<CastFocusClientAura>();
   aura::client::SetFocusClient(root_window, focus_client_.get());
